{
  "name": "velveteen",
  "description": "Warm bell-keys glowing through tape haze — a nostalgic celesta lullaby from a half-remembered summer. Soft celesta bell-keys with gentle tape wow and warm low-pass haze, Boards-of-Canada dreampop: hazy-bright like sunlight through old film, tender and happy. A tape-warm sub-key grounds the floor; a celesta lead sings a nostalgic tune with a higher key echoing it dreamily; a muffled warm key fills the cozy middle; clear glass-key chimes and tiny high glints shimmer through the haze; a lush hazy bloom and a detuned bell-key cluster wash underneath; a faint tape hiss-and-wow grain sits behind everything; and a tender little flick accents the bright. A major pentatonic @ A=432, additive and clean, never dreary, never harsh.",
  "drone": null,
  "master_gain": 0.45,
  "drone_gain": 0.0,
  "reverb_scale": 1.0,
